  "time_ut": 1657634419,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd2 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3\u0db8 \u0daf\u0dda \u0db8\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf \u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The best thing that can be done to calm the people is for Mahinda to say goodbye to politics",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Parliamentarian Patali Champika Ranawaka said that the only way to silence the people is for Mr. Mahinda Rajapaksa to leave politics completely.",
        "He also mentioned that if the Rajapaksas do not withdraw, the struggle will intensify and continue.",
        "Mr. Ranawaka said that the people did something that the opposition could not do and said that the Prime Minister should also leave after listening to the opinion of the people."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "Mahinda",
          "label": "PERSON"
        }
      ],
